        <div class="gallery-container">
            <!-- Mulching -->
            <div class="gallery">
              <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mulch">
                    <img src="images/tech-images/mulching.jpeg" alt="Mulching">
                  </a>
                <div class="desc">
                    <h2><u>Mulching</u></h2>
                    Mulching is one of the simplest and most beneficial practices you can use. Mulch helps conserve and extend available water, protects the soil from erosion, reduces competition, moderates temperature extremes, and acts as a barrier.
                </div>
            </div>
            <!-- Precision Agriculture -->
            <div class="gallery">
                <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Precision_agriculture">
                    <img src="images/tech-images/water_precision.jpeg" alt="Precision Agriculture">
                </a>
                <div class="desc">
                    <h2><u>Precision Agriculture</u></h2>
                    Precision agriculture, as the name implies, means application of precise and correct amounts of inputs like water, fertilizer, and pesticides at the correct time to the crop for increasing its productivity and maximizing its yields.
                </div>
            </div>
            <!-- Fog Collection -->
            <div class="gallery">
                <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fog_collection">
                    <img src="images/tech-images/fog_collector.jpeg" alt="Fog Collection">
                </a>
                <div class="desc">
                    <h2><u>Fog Collection</u></h2>
                    Fog collection is a method of harvesting water from fog using large vertical mesh nets. It is a sustainable technology that can provide fresh water for drinking, gardening, and afforestation.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="see-more">
            <a href="/content">See More</a>
        </div>
